title: A Case of Dermal Nerve Sheath Myxoma: A Different Tumor from Cellular Neurothekeoma.
label: Figure 1
caption: Firm, skin-color, irregular papule on left palm.

title: A Case of Dermal Nerve Sheath Myxoma: A Different Tumor from Cellular Neurothekeoma.
label: Figure 2
caption: Histopathologic image of lesion showed mutiple well-defined nodules of varying sizes with large amounts of mucin and few scattered cells in dermis (Hematoxylin & eosin x40).

title: A Case of Dermal Nerve Sheath Myxoma: A Different Tumor from Cellular Neurothekeoma.
label: Figure 3
caption: Higher image showing nests of few scattered spindled, stellate cells (Hematoxylin & eosin x200).

title: A Case of Dermal Nerve Sheath Myxoma: A Different Tumor from Cellular Neurothekeoma.
label: Figure 4
caption: Immunohistochemistry panel: positive for S100 (Hematoxylin & eosin x200);

title: A Case of Dermal Nerve Sheath Myxoma: A Different Tumor from Cellular Neurothekeoma.
label: Figure 5
caption: positive for Vimentin (Hematoxylin & eosin x200);

title: A Case of Dermal Nerve Sheath Myxoma: A Different Tumor from Cellular Neurothekeoma.
label: Figure 6
caption: Ki-67 labelling index <5% (Hematoxylin & eosin x100);

title: A Case of Dermal Nerve Sheath Myxoma: A Different Tumor from Cellular Neurothekeoma.
label: Figure 7
caption: negative for GFAP (Hematoxylin & eosin x200); it was also negative for CD34, CD10, CEA, and PCK.
